56d5ce02-ed9d-46b8-bdca-39aafddda850.0011e780-8706-4fa3-a8f3-1f9ca7ec886f.description=
This subflow was created by the Web Services Wizard to invoke the logout operation on file\:/C\:/Users/bob.howell/Documents/na.api.wsdl.922.txt. Note that the inputs to this flow which correspond to web service inputs are optional inputs.  This is due to the fact that web services definitions usually incorrectly indicate that too many inputs are required, and mirroring those settings in the flow would force you to enter unused values when running the flow.  The xmlTemplate input on the Invoke Method 2 step of this flow contains a template of the xml message to be sent, and the fields preceded by the comment "<\!--Optional\:-->" or "<\!--zero or more repetitions-->" are those which the web service indicates are optional; all others are indicated to be required.

Inputs\:
host - The host that is running the web service
port - The port on the host running the web service
DropNullElements - The input named RequestHeader|DropNullElements of the complex type\: RequestHeader
sessionid - The input named logout|parameters|sessionid of the complex type\: logout|parameters

Responses\:
success - The SOAP command was accepted by the web service
failure - Something went wrong while making the SOAP request

Extra Results\:
document - The raw XML response of the web service
documentStripped - The XML response of the web service stripped of namespaces
ResultSet - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/logoutResponse/Result/ResultSet
StackTrace - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/logoutResponse/Result/StackTrace/text()
Status - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/logoutResponse/Result/Status/text()
Text - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/logoutResponse/Result/Text/text()

56d5ce02-ed9d-46b8-bdca-39aafddda850.9399d4a1-919a-4e94-b6d3-5a051dc12d02.description=This flow checks for possible base64 encoded data, if found strips CR and LF, then attempts to decode it. If data contains a null, or if decode fails, or if data contains "Run Command Script" text original data is returned unchanged. Inputs\: data - the reaults from the "Execute NA command script" flow Results\: data - either unchanged or base64 decoded into readable text Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. failure - Something went wrong. 56d5ce02-ed9d-46b8-bdca-39aafddda850.cced42d7-f00e-4b7d-8c89-5a5985c1855d.description=Execute specified command script on NA server Inputs\: host - hostname of NA server port - NA API port (443) comment - Comment to add to script execution, in format of "OO PA Change Ticket \# for device " name - Name of command script to execute nowait - 1, meaning job should not wait if there is another job running on he target device phost - Target device name priority - Task priority (1) sessionid - Connection session to issue command through sync - 1, meaning call returns a response only after the job has completed variables - input parameters to be passed into script Results\: scriptOutput - Results of command script execution stackTrace - Error thrown by command script execution if any verification - Change ticket verification notes section with scriptOutput and stackTrace appended 56d5ce02-ed9d-46b8-bdca-39aafddda850.description=The "Run NA Show Command Scripts" flow is requested from Viewpoint using OO Central's Web Service's runFlowEx operation. This flow will pass its flow inputs to NA where the command script will run and return the command script output in the Web Service response naShowCommandResults field within rawResult. Inputs\: host - hostname of NA server phost - the name of the NA device name - the NA command script variables - zero or more parameters associated with the NA Command script (name) Results\: naShowCommandResults \= the results of the NA command script (part of the Viewpoint response from this flow) Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. failure - Something went wrong. 56d5ce02-ed9d-46b8-bdca-39aafddda850.f48c6e97-6e26-4ae1-b881-2cf4cdfe3fae.description=
